docs.lead_paragraph: A visit from President Tito of Yugoslavia to any country in the Western Hemisphere would be expected to arouse excitement. He has already met trouble in Brazil, his first stop in Latin America. Governors Lacerda of Guanabara, which contains Rio de Janeiro, and de Barros of Sao Paulo refused to receive him.
